-- EPA Issues First Air-Pollution Standards for Natural Gas Wells
-- B y   M a r k   D r a j e m   a n d   J i m   E f s t a t h i o u
-- 2012-04-18T17:09:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/epa-issues-first-air-pollution-standards-for-natural-gas-wells.html
The U.S. Environmental Protection
Agency issued its first regulations for natural-gas drilling,
which will reduce smog-forming compounds and pollutants,  Gina
McCarthy , the assistant administrator of the Environmental
Protection Agency, said today.  McCarthy said on a conference call that the rules
are cost-effective for the industry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Drajem in Washington at 
